{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictMode","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"Strict Mode","role":"collectionGroup","modules":[{"name":"VRMMetalKit"}],"roleHeading":"API Collection"},"kind":"article","topicSections":[{"title":"Configuration","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RendererConfig\/strict","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RenderFilter","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RendererConfig\/renderFilter"],"anchor":"Configuration"},{"title":"Errors","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictModeError"],"anchor":"Errors"},{"title":"Related","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RendererConfig","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/VRMRenderer"],"anchor":"Related"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/vrmmetalkit\/strictmode"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Validation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RenderFilter","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictValidator","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/ResourceIndices","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/MetalSizeConstants"],"anchor":"Validation","generated":true}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit"],["doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit","doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RenderingAvatars"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strict mode is the renderer’s built-in validation layer. It checks the structural correctness of every frame: that buffer and texture indices fall inside the argument table, that vertex buffers are large enough for the vertex count and stride a primitive declares, that the Swift-side uniform structs match their Metal counterparts byte-for-byte, that joint and morph indices stay inside their declared ranges, and that no draw call is silently empty. It does "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"not","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" check shader source correctness, nor does it diff pixel output — those belong to the Metal compiler and to your visual regression harness respectively."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strict mode is configured once, at renderer construction, via "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RendererConfig\/strict","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". The level you pick is a policy decision about how aggressively validation should interrupt the frame. Leave it at "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel\/off","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" in production, raise it to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel\/warn","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" while a feature is in active development, and pin it to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel\/fail","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" inside test suites so a regression in binding layout fails the test rather than silently rendering black."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"The three levels","anchor":"The-three-levels"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel\/off","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — production default. Validators still log to the package’s logging hooks, but no errors are collected and nothing is thrown. Zero observable overhead in a release build."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel\/warn","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — every violation is logged with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[StrictMode.warn]"},{"type":"text","text":" prefix and collected into a per-frame error list. The frame still completes. At end-of-frame, the validator emits a one-line summary of how many errors fired. Use this in CI smoke tests and integration runs."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictLevel\/fail","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — the first violation throws "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictModeError","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" out of the encoder. The frame is abandoned. Use this in unit tests and during local debugging so a regression surfaces with a stack trace at its source instead of as a missing draw call."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Enabling strict mode","anchor":"Enabling-strict-mode"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import VRMMetalKit","import Metal","","let device = MTLCreateSystemDefaultDevice()!","let config = RendererConfig(strict: .fail)","let renderer = VRMRenderer(device: device, config: config)","\/\/ Any binding or draw-call violation now throws StrictModeError."]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Narrowing with RenderFilter","anchor":"Narrowing-with-RenderFilter"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When you already know which mesh or material is misbehaving, set ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RendererConfig\/renderFilter","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RenderFilter","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" value to skip every draw call except the matching one. The three cases — ","type":"text"},{"code":".mesh(name)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".material(name)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".primitive(index)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — pair well with the adjacent debug knobs ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RendererConfig\/drawUntil","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/RendererConfig\/drawOnlyIndex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", which bisect by sorted-draw-list position. All three are diagnostic-only; leave them ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in production.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"What gets validated","anchor":"What-gets-validated"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Shader function presence in the library — "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictModeError\/missingVertexFunction(name:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictModeError\/missingFragmentFunction(name:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictModeError\/missingComputeFunction(name:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Pipeline-state creation — ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/VRMMetalKit\/documentation\/VRMMetalKit\/StrictModeError\/pipelineCreationFailed(_:)","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"para